HEADWORD: hangover
<hw>hangover</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An unpleasant feeling,
such as a headache, occurring as an aftereffect from the use of drugs
(especially alcohol).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>an official who remains in office after his
term.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> holdover.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hank</ent>⟦br⟧
